A fire has destroyed a company premises at Stanger Street in Durban Central. Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene to find Durban Fire Department fighting the fire. Thanks to excellent work by them the blaze was contained quickly, and no injuries were reported. The premises was severely damaged as it had multiple vehicles inside it. SAPS Search and Rescue were also in attendance.
At this stage the events leading up to the fire are unknown however SAPS and Durban Fire Department will be investigating further